[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_q65at")
reagent_id = "O2"
title = "Oxygen"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]O₂[/cell]
[cell]Element:[/cell][cell]Oxygen[/cell]
[cell]Atomic number:[/cell][cell]8[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]32 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Gas[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Colorless[/cell]
[cell]Smell:[/cell][cell]Odorless[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Supports combustion (helps substances burn).  
• Necessary for respiration of most living organisms.  
• Reacts with many elements to form oxides.
[b]Where oxygen is found[/b]
• About 21% of Earth’s atmosphere.  
• In water (H₂O).  
• In many minerals and rocks (oxides, silicates).
[b]Uses[/b]
• Breathing oxygen in medicine.  
• Used in steel production.  
• Rocket oxidizer in liquid oxygen form.
[b]Safety[/b]
Oxygen itself does not burn, but it makes fires burn stronger."
